{
  "text": "Converging data from animal models and human imaging studies support the hypothesis that Alzheimer's disease spreads through interconnected neural networks [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In transgenic mice, neurofibrillary pathology appears to spread sequentially from synapse to synapse, ultimately reflecting the pattern of structural connectivity [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
